  "texts": [
    "Perlman's(2022) was the only study to ask ChatGPT to draft a complaint, which, unsurprisingly, resulted in a very short complaint being drafted.",
    "We note that neither they, nor Iu and Wong (2023), engaged in any documented attempts to refine their prompts.",
    "Perlman (2022) used the following prompt: \"Draft a legal complaint for a Massachusetts state court by John Doe against Jane Smith for injuries arising out of a car accident on January 1, 2022 caused by Jane Smith at the intersection of Tremont Street and Park Street in Boston.",
    "The complaint should specify that Jane Smith failed to stop at a red light and caused John Smith serious injuries.\"",
    "For drafting essays, Choi et al. (2023) asked ChatGPT to write essays section by section; we use a similar prompting approach in this study."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Perlman's(2022) was the only study to ask ChatGPT to draft a complaint, which, unsurprisingly, resulted in a very short complaint being drafted.",
